The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cDot11sMesh.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cDot11sMesh.description: The file defines a MIB to provide MESH configuration information. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Mesh A network consisting of two or more mesh points which communicate with each other via mesh services. Mesh Point (MP) An IEEE 802.11 entity that contains an IEEE 802.11-conformant medium access control (MAC) and physical layer (PHY) interface to the wireless medium (WM) that supports mesh services. Mesh Access Point (MAP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more access points. Mesh Portal Point (MPP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more portals. Mesh Link A link between two MPs.

h3cDot11sMeshMkdID.name: h3cDot11sMeshMkdID
h3cDot11sMeshMkdID.description: This object represents the mesh key distributor identifier (MKD-ID). If the MKD-ID is not configured, the value is '00:00:00:00:00:00'.

h3cDot11sMeshPflTable.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflTable
h3cDot11sMeshPflTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh profile. A mesh profile is created and mapped to a MP so that it can provide mesh services to other MPs which have the same mesh ID. When the mesh profile is enabled, all of the object in this table can not be modified except h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable. The mesh profile can not be deleted when it is bound with the radio.

h3cDot11sMeshPflEntry.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflEntry
h3cDot11sMeshPflEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a mesh profile.

h3cDot11sMeshPflIndex.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflIndex
h3cDot11sMeshPflIndex.description: This object represents the index of the mesh profile.

h3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID
h3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID.description: This object represents the mesh ID of the mesh profile. The string length of this object is zero when the mesh ID is not configured. If the mesh ID is not configured, h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

h3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum
h3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.description: This object represents the specified mesh interface number binding to the mesh profile. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed. If the mesh interface is not specified, the value of h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

h3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive
h3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.description: This object represents the mesh link keep-alive interval.

h3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate
h3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.description: This object represents the link backhaul rate.

h3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.name: h3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable
h3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh key distributor (MKD) service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The MKD service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The MKD service for the mesh profile is disabled.

h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable
h3cDot11sMeshPflEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The mesh profile is disabled.

h3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus
h3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyTable.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyTable
h3cDot11sMpPlcyTable.description: This table is used to configure MP policy. There is 'default_mp_plcy' on system by default and its index is 1. The 'default_mp_plcy' can not be deleted or modified. The MP policy can not be deleted when it is applied to a radio. It can not be modified when it is applied to an enabled radio.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry
h3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a MP policy.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex
h3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex.description: This object represents the MP policy index.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyName.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyName
h3cDot11sMpPlcyName.description: This object represents the MP policy name. MP policy can not be created with name 'a', 'al', 'all' or 'default_mp_plcy'. Modification is not supported.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable
h3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.description: This object indicates whether the link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'true': The link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'false': The link initiation for the MP policy is disabled.

h3cDot11sMlspEnable.name: h3cDot11sMlspEnable
h3cDot11sMlspEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh link switch protocol (MLSP) is enabled. 'true': MLSP is enabled. 'false': MLSP is disabled.

h3cDot11sProbReqInterval.name: h3cDot11sProbReqInterval
h3cDot11sProbReqInterval.description: This object represents the probe request interval.

h3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable.name: h3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable
h3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable.description: This object indicates whether the device can play as the role of an authenticator.

h3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.name: h3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI
h3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.description: This object represents the link-hold receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

h3cDot11sLinkHoldTime.name: h3cDot11sLinkHoldTime
h3cDot11sLinkHoldTime.description: This object represents the link-hold time.

h3cDot11sSwitchMargin.name: h3cDot11sSwitchMargin
h3cDot11sSwitchMargin.description: This object represents the link-switch margin.

h3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.name: h3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI
h3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.description: This object represents the link saturation receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

h3cDot11sLinkRateMode.name: h3cDot11sLinkRateMode
h3cDot11sLinkRateMode.description: This object represents the rate mode of the mesh link.

h3cDot11sMaxLinkNum.name: h3cDot11sMaxLinkNum
h3cDot11sMaxLinkNum.description: This object represents the maximum number of the mesh link.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus
h3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11sMlspCfgTable.name: h3cDot11sMlspCfgTable
h3cDot11sMlspCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure MLSP proxy MAC address. Only if the specified MP policy is modifiable and the MLSP is enabled, the row of this table can be created and deleted. The row of this table can not be modified.

h3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry.name: h3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry
h3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of MLSP proxy MAC address.

h3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex.name: h3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex
h3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address index.

h3cDot11sMlspProxyMac.name: h3cDot11sMlspProxyMac
h3cDot11sMlspProxyMac.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address.

h3cDot11sMlspRowStatus.name: h3cDot11sMlspRowStatus
h3cDot11sMlspRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11sRadioCfgTable.name: h3cDot11sRadioCfgTable
h3cDot11sRadioCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified radio.

h3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry.name: h3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry
h3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified radio.

h3cDot11sMeshPflMap.name: h3cDot11sMeshPflMap
h3cDot11sMeshPflMap.description: This object represents the number of the mesh profile mapped to the specified radio. The value is zero when the radio is not binding mesh profile.

h3cDot11sMpPlcyMap.name: h3cDot11sMpPlcyMap
h3cDot11sMpPlcyMap.description: This object represents the index of the MP policy mapped to the specified radio. The MP policy is 'default_mp_plcy' when the radio is not binding user-defined MP policy. The index of 'default_mp_plcy' is 1. This object can not be modified when the radio is enabled.

h3cDot11sAPCfgTable.name: h3cDot11sAPCfgTable
h3cDot11sAPCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified AP.

h3cDot11sAPCfgEntry.name: h3cDot11sAPCfgEntry
h3cDot11sAPCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified AP.

h3cDot11sPortalEnable.name: h3cDot11sPortalEnable
h3cDot11sPortalEnable.description: This object indicates whether the portal service is enabled. 'true': The portal service is enabled. 'false': The portal service is disabled.

h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacTable.name: h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacTable
h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacTable.description: This table is used to configure wireless distribution system (WDS). The row of this table can not be modified.

h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacAddrss.name: h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacAddrss

h3cDot11sWDSPeerMacRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.
